# Copy this file to `.env.local` and fill in the path to enable local deck loading.
# `.env.local` is gitignored; this `.env.example` is the only committed env file (documentation only).
#
# Absolute path to a case deck JSON. During `npm run dev`, Vite serves this file at /casedeck.json,
# and the app loads it on first run (and auto-refreshes when its deckVersion is newer). The deck file
# must live OUTSIDE this repo so its contents can never be committed or built into dist/.
# If this is unset or the file is missing, the app starts in its empty/demo state.
#
# Example (Windows): SOURCEDECK_DECK_PATH=C:\path\to\your-casedeck.json
SOURCEDECK_DECK_PATH=
